Legs
. Apical dorsal spine of protibia weakly arcuate. Dorsal surface of mesotibia without spicules, the tibia bearing only 4 short apical pegs. Metacoxa 1.72× as long as wide, punctulate along lower margin of dorsal surface (
Fig. 44
). Metafemur moderately sparsely punctulate on disc, the interspaces between points at least as wide as their own diameter. Tarsal groove of metatibia visible on apical half of the distance between base of tibia and tarsal insertion. Tibia with 2 rows of subelliptic areoles along tarsal groove (
Fig. 45
). Claws with two pegs and a long seta on ventral margin (
Fig. 20
).

Diagnosis
. Body with large parts brownish to reddish, not black (
Fig. 39
). Fore wing mostly hyaline, hardly infuscate towards apex (
Fig. 46
). Setation silvery on entire body (
Fig. 39
). Frons with adpressed setation covering integument only dorsally; sparser and suberect setation visible ventrally on frons and gena (
Fig. 40
). Mandibles strongly tapering. Teeth on vertex completely absent. Antenna black (
Fig. 42
). All funiculars distinctly longer than wide. Pronotal carina absent (
Fig. 43
). Pronotal collum with 3 patches of dense, adpressed setation (
Fig. 41
).
